  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">More than 25 million people have been affected by severe flooding across India, Nepal, Bangladesh, Pakistan, Afghanistan, and Myanmar during the 2020 monsoon season. Recent floods have taken the lives of 550 people across the region due to storm waters and landslides. One-third of Bangladesh&apos;s delta region remains under water, and 300,000 individuals in India&apos;s Bihar state have been evacuated to relief camps. This fund will provide immediate relief to survivors and support long-term recovery.</narrative>
  </description>
